<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Question:</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> What is the advised print mode for a typical Application/Media?
</p><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Answer:</b>
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Media in combination with gloss and matte pint modes:
</p><fig id="GUID-DC8C7AA7-4A81-4E52-97FF-5B49128D0718" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-CA2D5AD9-D389-46A9-A887-46B9116D2144-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-CA2D5AD9-D389-46A9-A887-46B9116D2144-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">* Matte and mixed matte/gloss print modes can only be used if the <ph translate="no" class="- topic/ph ">FLXfinish<sup class="+ topic/ph hi-d/sup ">+</sup></ph> license is installed.
</p><p class="- topic/p ">** For Film -frontlit/rollup-, in gloss mode, the quality is heavily media dependent by wrinkle or inkspread.
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Uncoated paper: gloss print mode is not recommended because the curing quality is not guaranteed.
</p></section><section id="GUID-271615A6-BA63-4E09-80EB-2DC9AD73386D" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> 
